        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 6:52PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 651 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Abbeville, or near Shoals Junction, moving east at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ware Shoals, Due West, Cokesbury, Hodges, and Shoals Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
